1166
01:34:12,450 --> 01:34:14,560
For Christ sakes, Ava,
it's just a present.

1167
01:34:14,665 --> 01:34:18,019
You can't buy me, Howard,
so stop trying.

1168
01:34:18,123 --> 01:34:21,648
Don't buy me any more diamonds or
sapphires or any other goddamn thing.

1169
01:34:21,752 --> 01:34:24,944
You can buy me dinner.
How about that?

1170
01:34:25,048 --> 01:34:26,370
Jesus, Ava.

1171
01:34:27,210 --> 01:34:30,407
It's bad enough I have to endure
those filthy gym shoes of yours,

1172
01:34:30,512 --> 01:34:35,495
but then I get all dolled up and we have
to go out in this old jalopy without a hood.

1173
01:34:35,599 --> 01:34:38,791
Ava, will you marry me?

1174
01:34:38,895 --> 01:34:40,210
No, Howard.

1175
01:34:40,314 --> 01:34:44,425
- Why not, for heaven's sake?
- In the first place, I don't love you.

1176
01:34:44,529 --> 01:34:46,967
In the second place, I'm still married.

1177
01:34:47,071 --> 01:34:51,848
Look, you got girls stashed all over town.
You got a damn harem just at the Bel-Air.

1178
01:34:51,952 --> 01:34:53,904
Why don't you marry
one of your bungalow girls?

1179
01:34:54,029 --> 01:34:56,312
Those are employees.
I'm not going to marry an employee.

1180
01:34:56,417 --> 01:34:59,319
Jesus Christ, how would that look?

1181
01:35:04,915 --> 01:35:07,406
Good Lord, what is going on?

1182
01:35:10,629 --> 01:35:13,334
- Oh, my God.
- Goddamn it.

1183
01:35:14,841 --> 01:35:16,041
Faith.

1184
01:35:16,893 --> 01:35:18,955
- Faith. What the hell?
- Look out.

1185
01:35:19,059 --> 01:35:22,008
Goddamn, what the hell are you doing?

1186
01:35:24,851 --> 01:35:27,715
- You OK, lady?
- What are you doing with her?

1187
01:35:27,819 --> 01:35:30,554
We're going to dinner, that's all.
Now get out of there.

1188
01:35:30,658 --> 01:35:32,719
Get that crazy bitch away from me.

1189
01:35:32,823 --> 01:35:36,225
- Don't you love me any more?
- Course I love you, pork chop.

1190
01:35:36,330 --> 01:35:38,558
- Ava, look over here.
- Howard.

1191
01:35:38,662 --> 01:35:40,899
- Hey.
- Come on, Howard.

1192
01:35:44,246 --> 01:35:46,550
Juan Trippe is working with
that goddamn Senator Brewster now.

1193
01:35:46,654 --> 01:35:47,482
They're after you, Howard.

1194
01:35:47,587 --> 01:35:50,740
If the Community Airline Bill becomes law,
we are finished, my friend.

1195
01:35:50,844 --> 01:35:53,140
Pan Am will have a legal monopoly
on international travel.

1196
01:35:53,244 --> 01:35:55,616
How can they justify it, Jack?
It's un-American.

1197
01:35:55,720 --> 01:35:58,062
Senator Brewster's saying that
nationalised foreign carriers,

1198
01:35:58,166 --> 01:35:59,538
like Air France and Lufthansa,

1199
01:35:59,642 --> 01:36:02,500
can offer lower rates
cos they don't have to compete, right?

1200
01:36:02,604 --> 01:36:04,777
So, hey, let's just get rid of
all that messy competition

1201
01:36:04,881 --> 01:36:07,759
and have a nationalised airline of our own,
and why don't we make it Pan Am?

1202
01:36:07,863 --> 01:36:09,636
I'm not kowtowing to Washington
or anyone else.

1203
01:36:09,740 --> 01:36:11,716
- Howard, I need you up here.
- One sec, Odie.

1204
01:36:11,820 --> 01:36:14,595
Look, we are Trans World Airlines,
all right?

1205
01:36:14,699 --> 01:36:19,265
Get me something with a circle or a globe
or something round, for God's sake.

1206
01:36:19,370 --> 01:36:22,106
Speak up. I know.
I don't give a rat's ass what he says.

1207
01:36:22,210 --> 01:36:25,109
I'm not making a single cut.
Tell him I'm releasing without a seal.

1208
01:36:25,213 --> 01:36:26,941
All right.
We gotta go public with this.

1209
01:36:27,045 --> 01:36:29,051
I'm gonna talk to Hearst,
see what press he can give me,

1210
01:36:29,155 --> 01:36:31,136
but sooner or later it's gonna come down
to a vote in the Senate,

1211
01:36:31,241 --> 01:36:32,367
so we gotta get senators on our side.

1212
01:36:32,471 --> 01:36:35,078
- What do you want me to do?
- Do what Trippe does, for Christ sake.

1213
01:36:35,182 --> 01:36:36,450
Set up some offshore operations.

1214
01:36:36,554 --> 01:36:38,811
See who's up for re-election.
Let's start making donations.

1215
01:36:38,915 --> 01:36:42,291
- So, you want me to bribe senators?
- I don't want them bribed, Jack.

1216
01:36:42,396 --> 01:36:45,001
I want it done legally.
I want them bought.

1217
01:36:45,106 --> 01:36:47,027
And put a team of investigators
on Senator Brewster.

1218
01:36:47,132 --> 01:36:49,633
I need to know everything there is to know
about that shit bag.

1219
01:36:49,737 --> 01:36:52,720
Where he goes, what he says
and who he screws.

1220
01:36:52,824 --> 01:36:56,018
- Get into it right now, Jack.
- You got it.

1221
01:37:02,532 --> 01:37:05,284
Just give me a second.

1222
01:37:06,203 --> 01:37:09,816
- All right. What do you need?
- Rudder and elevators.

1223
01:37:09,920 --> 01:37:14,737
These are fine. Have Simon and Pete get
back to me on the hydraulic assemblies.

1224
01:37:14,842 --> 01:37:18,615
- We need a secondary system here.
- OK.

1225
01:37:18,719 --> 01:37:21,579
And listen, we need to take
another look at the wheel.

1226
01:37:21,683 --> 01:37:26,167
- Jesus. The damn wheel?
- Yeah. It just doesn't feel right.

1227
01:37:26,271 --> 01:37:30,466
Christ almighty, you've seen 8,000
goddamn wheels. Choose one, please.

1228
01:37:30,570 --> 01:37:32,298
- Just one of them.
- I know. I know.

1229
01:37:32,402 --> 01:37:34,798
- This one?
- I know. This one...

1230
01:37:34,902 --> 01:37:37,013
This one's pretty close.

1231
