I'm losing starboard engine.

1304
01:44:19,518 --> 01:44:22,458
Increasing power to 2800 rpm.

1305
01:44:22,562 --> 01:44:24,210
Cutting back.

1306
01:44:24,314 --> 01:44:26,514
Increasing starboard engine only.

1307
01:44:27,603 --> 01:44:30,760
Cutting back.
I'm losing altitude.

1308
01:44:30,864 --> 01:44:34,385
Howard, check starboard engine
manifold pressure.

1309
01:44:34,490 --> 01:44:37,809
- It's good, but rpms are low.
- Are both starboard props turning?

1310
01:44:37,913 --> 01:44:39,513
Hold on.

1311
01:44:39,707 --> 01:44:42,728
It looks like they are, but she's pulling me
back and starboard, Odie.

1312
01:44:42,832 --> 01:44:46,521
- How bad is your cross control?
- I'm at full left rudder and full left aileron,

1313
01:44:46,626 --> 01:44:49,069
but she won't stay level.
Goddamn it.

1314
01:44:49,173 --> 01:44:52,157
- Howard, give us your position.
- 2,000 feet over...

1315
01:44:52,262 --> 01:44:56,325
Oh, Christ, I don't know.
Beverly Hills. 1,500 feet.

1316
01:44:56,429 --> 01:44:58,250
We're going down.

1317
01:44:59,134 --> 01:45:02,747
I'm gonna try for the Wilshire Country
Club. Ninth hole. You reading me?

1318
01:45:02,851 --> 01:45:06,891
Wilshire Country Club. Copy that.
Howard, reduce engines to one thousand.

1319
01:45:07,517 --> 01:45:09,965
I'm going down.

1320
01:45:10,069 --> 01:45:12,553
I'm not gonna make it, buddy.

1321
01:45:18,779 --> 01:45:19,941
Goddamn it.

1322
01:47:23,153 --> 01:47:26,644
Is there anyone else inside?
Is there anyone else?

1323
01:47:26,748 --> 01:47:27,348
No.

1324
01:47:32,246 --> 01:47:35,192
I'm Howard Hughes, the aviator.

1325
01:47:35,296 --> 01:47:36,896
Come on.

1326
01:47:44,591 --> 01:47:47,832
Every inch of wiring and fluid connection...

1327
01:47:47,936 --> 01:47:50,625
He has burns to 78 per cent of his body.

1328
01:47:50,730 --> 01:47:53,797
Nine ribs are shattered.
Not broken, shattered.

1329
01:47:53,902 --> 01:47:58,426
As are his nose, his chin, his cheek,
his left knee, his left elbow.

1330
01:47:58,530 --> 01:48:01,635
He has 60 lacerations on his face
to the bone.

1331
01:48:01,740 --> 01:48:04,597
His chest was crushed,
so his left lung has collapsed

1332
01:48:04,701 --> 01:48:09,146
and his heart has shifted entirely
to the right side of his chest cavity.

1333
01:48:09,250 --> 01:48:11,144
Jesus, God.

1334
01:48:11,248 --> 01:48:14,606
He's getting blood transfusions now, but...

1335
01:48:14,710 --> 01:48:18,196
- Whose blood?
- I'm sorry?

1336
01:48:18,300 --> 01:48:21,616
- Whose blood?
- From our stock.

1337
01:48:21,720 --> 01:48:23,576
He's not gonna like that.

1338
01:48:23,680 --> 01:48:29,371
Mr Dietrich, I doubt he's ever
gonna like or dislike anything again.

1339
01:48:29,476 --> 01:48:31,842
I'm terribly sorry.

1340
01:49:00,081 --> 01:49:02,068
Orange juice.

1341
01:49:02,172 --> 01:49:03,572
It's...

1342
01:49:05,012 --> 01:49:08,253
It's not fresh from the kitchen, so I...

1343
01:49:09,299 --> 01:49:13,427
I have them make it here so I can see.

1344
01:49:18,516 --> 01:49:20,592
Look at me.

1345
01:49:23,104 --> 01:49:26,800
I'm a monster.
Yeah.

1346
01:49:26,904 --> 01:49:30,600
Orange juice has nutritional value.

1347
01:49:31,654 --> 01:49:36,983
There's some flies
outside my window, though.

1348
01:49:37,087 --> 01:49:38,087
So...

1349
01:49:40,872 --> 01:49:42,948
little Howard likes...

1350
01:49:44,876 --> 01:49:46,276
citrus.

1351
01:49:47,927 --> 01:49:49,997
Don't he just?

1352
01:49:52,926 --> 01:49:54,526
Tell me.

1353
01:49:56,271 --> 01:50:00,125
An oil seal ripped off
the starboard rear propeller.

1354
01:50:00,229 --> 01:50:04,132
When the pressure dropped,
the prop reversed pitch.

1355
01:50:04,236 --> 01:50:06,427
Do you understand me?

1356
01:50:06,531 --> 01:50:11,512
Howard, I'm sorry to have to tell you
this now, but there's something else.

1357
01:50:11,616 --> 01:50:14,067
- You following me?
- Yeah.

1358
01:50:15,865 --> 01:50:21,692
The Air Force cancelled
the contract on the Hercules.

1359
01:50:21,796 --> 01:50:27,487
The war's over now,
and they say they don't need it any more.

1360
01:50:27,592 --> 01:50:32,203
I have to know what you want me to do.
Should I release the staff?

1361
01:50:32,307 --> 01:50:34,307
How far...

1362
01:50:34,805 --> 01:50:37,755
from finishing?

1363
01:50:38,930 --> 01:50:41,671
- About six months.
- No, no.

1364
01:50:41,776 --> 01:50:43,576
In money.

1365
01:50:47,022 --> 01:50:51,102
Seven million.
Maybe more.

1366
01:50:56,823 --> 01:50:58,623
Build it.

1367
01:50:59,752 --> 01:51:02,752
Build it, Odie.

1368
01:51:03,587 --> 01:51:04,987
Howard,

1369
