a Constellation crashed
outside Reading, Pennsylvania.

1370
01:51:09,845 --> 01:51:13,703
The Civil Aeronautics Board
has grounded the whole fleet.

1371
01:51:23,641 --> 01:51:29,727
You know, Juan Trippe sent me flowers.

1372
01:51:31,816 --> 01:51:33,892
Take a look.

1373
01:51:37,405 --> 01:51:42,311
- What did you do with all the others?
- I had them taken out.

1374
01:51:42,415 --> 01:51:45,613
They attract aphids.

1375
01:51:46,623 --> 01:51:52,033
Aphids are...
They're just awful little creatures.

1376
01:51:52,138 --> 01:51:53,338
But...

1377
01:51:56,216 --> 01:51:58,292
But these ones...

1378
01:51:59,469 --> 01:52:03,597
I wanted to see these ones every day.

1379
01:52:10,689 --> 01:52:13,763
Can white elephants really fly?
That's everybody's question.

1380
01:52:13,868 --> 01:52:16,638
It's the hull of the world's
mightiest airplane,

1381
01:52:16,742 --> 01:52:19,100
a flying boat built
by Howard Hughes.

1382
01:52:19,204 --> 01:52:23,353
220 feet long, it towers higher
than a five-storey building.

1383
01:52:23,458 --> 01:52:27,524
Power lines have to be cut as it starts
the trip from Culver City, California,

1384
01:52:27,628 --> 01:52:29,775
to the Pacific, 30 miles away.

1385
01:52:29,880 --> 01:52:33,199
Moving the 60-ton load
is quite an engineering problem.

1386
01:52:33,303 --> 01:52:37,240
But you gotta ask, "Was anything this big
ever supposed to fly?"

1387
01:52:37,344 --> 01:52:41,874
